  "author_association": "NONE",
  "body": "Tested with React 16.4 on Firefox 60 / macOS, the `onBlur` and `onFocus` don't bubble to the parent component when focusing / blurring the button by clicking on it / outside it.\r\n\r\n```jsx\r\nclass MyComponent extends React.Component {\r\n  render() {\r\n    return (\r\n      <div \r\n        onFocus={ e => console.log('focus') } \r\n        onBlur={ e => console.log('blur') }\r\n      >\r\n        <button>Click me</button>\r\n      </div>\r\n    );\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n(@AlmeroSteyn [writes here](https://github.com/reactjs/reactjs.org/pull/923#issuecomment-395319251) that they bubble correctly on Firefox/Windows)",
